Aim:
To store and display details of N students using array of objects.

Algorithm:
Start
Create a Student class with roll, name, and marks.
Declare an array of objects.
For each object, read details.
Display details of all students.
Stop.

program:
#include<iostream>
using namespace std;

class Student {
    int roll;
    string name;
    float marks;
public:
    void getData() {
        cout<<"Enter Roll Number: ";
        cin>>roll;
        cout<<"Enter Name: ";
        cin>>name;
        cout<<"Enter Marks: ";
        cin>>marks;
    }

    void display() {
        cout<<"\nRoll: "<<roll<<"  Name: "<<name<<"  Marks: "<<marks;
    }
};

int main() {
    int n;
    cout<<"Enter number of students: ";
    cin>>n;

    Student s[n];

    cout<<"\n--- Enter Student Details ---\n";
    for(int i=0; i<n; i++)
        s[i].getData();

    cout<<"\n--- Student Information ---\n";
    for(int i=0; i<n; i++)
        s[i].display();

    return 0;
}

Output:
Enter number of students: 2
Enter Roll Number: 1
Enter Name: Priya
Enter Marks: 89
Enter Roll Number: 2
Enter Name: Arjun
Enter Marks: 92

--- Student Information ---
Roll: 1 Name: Priya Marks: 89
Roll: 2 Name: Arjun Marks: 92

Result:
The program successfully stores and displays details of multiple students using array of objects.
The program successfully stores and displays details of multiple students using array of objects.
